{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772545790,"nonce":"ZeerpoOHeEkYqvZ6MymW+sYiqq8=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87va0fz","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/330","origin":"github"},"title":"Improve first-run initialization UX with interactive manifest setup","message":"## Context\n\nSpun out from #325 (ADR: Makefile vs just). Once the Makefile is refactored with stamp-file dependencies (so `make build` works from a fresh clone), the first-run experience should guide new users through workspace initialization.\n\n## Problem\n\nCurrently a fresh clone requires the user to know and run multiple commands in the correct order. With stamp-based Make handling the dependency graph, we have an opportunity to make the very first interaction intuitive and informative.\n\n## Requirements\n\nFrom [#325 comment](https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/325#issuecomment-3991163624):\n\n1. **Interactive manifest setup** — on first run (triggered by `make build` or a dedicated `make initialize` target), a script asks the user for a manifest repo location with options:\n   - Specify a path to an existing repo to clone (possibly local)\n   - Create a new manifest repo\n   - Default to `unh_marine_autonomy`\n2. **Non-interactive mode** — the initialization script accepts arguments to skip prompts (for CI and AI agents)\n3. **Verbose first-run output** — when running for the first time, explain the workspace layout (layers, manifest, overlays) to give the user context for the prompts\n4. **Optional example layers** — if creating a new manifest repo, optionally populate it with example layer configurations\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Depends on #325 (stamp-file Makefile) being completed first\n- Must work within the stamp-file dependency model\n- Should degrade gracefully if run non-interactively without arguments\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}